</exercise>

<exercise id="fs-id2688971" type="problems-exercises"><problem id="fs-id2661066"><para id="fs-id3046935">The formation of condensation on a glass of ice water causes the ice to melt faster than it would otherwise. If 8.00 g of condensation forms on a glass containing both water and 200 g of ice, how many grams of the ice will melt as a result? Assume no other heat transfer occurs.</para></problem>
