<glossary>
<definition id="fs-id1065507"><term>heat of sublimation</term><meaning id="fs-id2789825"> the energy required to change a substance from the solid phase to the vapor phase</meaning></definition>
<definition id="fs-id2228558"><term>latent heat coefficient</term><meaning id="fs-id2080163"> a physical constant equal to the amount of heat transferred for every 1 kg of a substance during the change in phase of the substance</meaning></definition>
<definition id="fs-id2910456"><term>sublimation</term><meaning id="fs-id1683059"> the transition from the solid phase to the vapor phase</meaning></definition>
</glossary>
